          "content": "Let's break down the expression step by step, following the order of operations (PEMDAS/BODMAS): Multiplication first, then Addition and Subtraction from left to right.\n\nThe expression is:\n$$((-9 + -3 + 6 - 8) - (-7 \\times -2 \\times -6 + -6))$$\n\n### Step 1: Evaluate the first set of parentheses\n$$( -9 + -3 + 6 - 8 )$$\n\n1.  $-9 + -3 = -12$\n2.  $-12 + 6 = -6$\n3.  $-6 - 8 = -14$\n\nSo, the first part equals **$-14$**.\n\n### Step 2: Evaluate the second set of parentheses\n$$( -7 \\times -2 \\times -6 + -6 )$$\n\n1.  Perform the multiplications first:\n    *   $-7 \\times -2 = 14$\n    *   $14 \\times -6 = -84$\n2.  Now perform the addition:\n    *   $-84 + -6 = -90$\n\nSo, the second part equals **$-90$**.\n\n### Step 3: Combine the results\nNow substitute the values back into the original expression:\n$$(-14) - (-90)$$\n\nSubtracting a negative number is the same as adding a positive number:\n$$-14 + 90$$\n$$90 - 14 = 76$$\n\n**Answer:**\n76\n",
